value.0: Captain Harlin has a reputation for being amongst one of the best smugglers on Viscara. She leads a tight crew, one that occasionally seeks outside help.
A smuggler who operates under Veles, he has a particular knack for getting his hands on interesting things.

The smugglers operating under Veles move everything from food through the Imperial blockade to armaments despite Czerka's suppression. There is no monolithic organization to the smugglers, and they range from individual operations to small crews, but they largely work off some unwritten code of honor to watch each others' back against greater powers that would see them stomped on. They are the underdogs, and underdogs band together, disparate as they may be.

The smugglers operating beneath Veles have collected caches of such armaments, stowing them where they may in their hideouts. While not normally contrabands when used by mercenaries and adventurers alike, Czerka has been tireless in trying to prevent the sale of these armaments to the horde of refugees and gangs that now populate the Slums and Industrial District. A game of cat and mouse has soon ensued, where Czerka tries to clamp down on these goods, while the smugglers ferry them under the megacorporation's very nose to supply the city's denizen...

The Bullfrog-class high capacity heavy delivery trucks are known throughout Viscara for their reliability. Manufactured locally in Veles, some of these have even been sold and shipped to other parts of the galaxy.

A sophisticated system of servo-motors and pulleys have been set up here, allowing the smugglers operating out of this hideout to raise and lower one of their Bullfrog delivery hover-trucks into a non-descript garage from where they could take in and dispatch some of their high-volume deliveries. The smuggling operations in Veles are incredibly profitable, and they have devised increasingly complex operations over the years to evade the reach of the rapacious Czerka Corporation.
